SearchEventLog.name: SearchEventLog
SearchEventLog.description: Search Event Log provides details about the user’s search query.

PrefixesSearched.description: A space-delineated list of key prefixes that are searched.

QueryIdentifier.description: Unique ID of the search query.

RequestIdentifier.description: The unique ID of a single transaction. A transaction can contain one or more events. Each event in a given transaction has the same RequestIdentifier. For example: 3nWgxWbDKWWDIk0FKfF5DV.

ResultCount.description: Number of results returned by the search query.

SearchQuery.description: The first 100 characters of the search query.

Timestamp.description: The access time of Salesforce services in GMT. For example, 2020-01-20T19:12:26.965Z. Milliseconds are the most granular setting.

UserIdentifier.description: The ID of the user who’s using Salesforce services through the UI or the API. For example: 00530000009M943.
